412→   412→#### Rule R-PROX-01: Duplicate POI Detection (addresses F-FAB-01)
413→   413→
414→   414→**Signals:**
415→   415→- Haversine distance between new submission and existing points of the same category
416→   416→- Name similarity (Levenshtein distance or fuzzy match)
417→   417→
418→   418→**Detection Logic:**
419→   419→
420→   420→```typescript
421→   421→async function checkDuplicatePoi(
422→   422→  category: SubmissionCategory,
423→   423→  location: SubmissionLocation,
424→   424→  name: string,
425→   425→  existingPoints: ProjectedPoint[]
426→   426→): Promise<'ok' | 'flag' | 'block'> {
427→   427→  const sameCategory = existingPoints.filter(p => p.category === category);
428→   428→
429→   429→  for (const point of sameCategory) {
430→   430→    const distanceKm = haversineKm(location, point.location);
431→   431→
432→   432→    // Two pharmacies within 20 meters is almost certainly a duplicate
433→   433→    if (distanceKm < 0.02) return 'block';
434→   434→
435→   435→    // Within 50 meters with similar name -> flag
436→   436→    if (distanceKm < 0.05) {
437→   437→      const existingName = point.details?.name ?? '';
438→   438→      if (fuzzyNameMatch(name, existingName) > 0.7) return 'block';
439→   439→      return 'flag';
440→   440→    }
441→   441→
442→   442→    // Within 100 meters -> flag
443→   443→    if (distanceKm < 0.1) return 'flag';
444→   444→  }
445→   445→
446→   446→  return 'ok';
447→   447→}
448→   448→```
449→   449→
450→   450→**Thresholds:**
451→   451→- Same category within 20m -> auto-reject (suggest enrichment instead)
452→   452→- Same category within 50m with similar name -> auto-reject
453→   453→- Same category within 100m -> flag for review
454→   454→- Same category within 200m -> add to submission risk score
455→   455→
456→   456→**Confidence:** 85% at 20m/same-category. 70% at 50m. In dense urban Douala, multiple mobile money kiosks within 100m is legitimate, so the 100m threshold is a flag, not a block.
457→   457→
458→   458→#### Rule R-DEV-01: Device Fingerprint Cross-Reference (addresses F-ACC-01, F-XP-04)
459→   459→
460→   460→**Signals:**
461→   461→- `clientDevice.deviceId` from `lib/client/deviceProfile.ts`
462→   462→- `clientDevice.userAgent`, `deviceMemoryGb`, `hardwareConcurrency`, `platform`
463→   463→- EXIF `deviceMake`, `deviceModel` from photo metadata
464→   464→
465→   465→**Detection Logic:**
466→   466→
467→   467→```typescript
468→   468→async function checkDeviceCrossReference(
469→   469→  userId: string,
470→   470→  deviceId: string,
471→   471→  deviceFingerprint: string // hash of userAgent + memory + cpu + platform
472→   472→): Promise<'ok' | 'flag'> {
473→   473→  // Check if this deviceId has been used by other userIds
474→   474→  const userIdsForDevice = await getUserIdsByDeviceId(deviceId);
475→   475→  const otherUsers = userIdsForDevice.filter(id => id !== userId);
476→   476→
477→   477→  if (otherUsers.length > 0) return 'flag'; // Multiple accounts on same device
478→   478→
479→   479→  // Check if this device fingerprint matches other accounts
480→   480→  const userIdsForFingerprint = await getUserIdsByFingerprint(deviceFingerprint);
481→   481→  const fpOtherUsers = userIdsForFingerprint.filter(id => id !== userId);
482→   482→
483→   483→  if (fpOtherUsers.length >= 2) return 'flag'; // 3+ accounts with same fingerprint
484→   484→
485→   485→  return 'ok';
486→   486→}
487→   487→```
488→   488→
489→   489→**Thresholds:**
490→   490→- Same deviceId used by 2+ userIds -> flag both accounts
491→   491→- Same deviceId used by 3+ userIds -> auto-suspend newest accounts
492→   492→- Same device fingerprint across 3+ userIds -> flag for alt-account investigation
493→   493→
494→   494→**Confidence:** 75%. Shared devices are common in Africa (family members, cybercafe computers). The flag-not-block approach is intentional.
495→   495→
496→   496→#### Rule R-ENR-01: Self-Enrichment Pattern (addresses F-XP-02)
497→   497→
498→   498→**Signals:**
499→   499→- Count of ENRICH_EVENTs by the same userId on the same pointId
500→   500→- Time gap between CREATE_EVENT and ENRICH_EVENTs
501→   501→- Whether the creating user is also the enriching user
502→   502→
503→   503→**Detection Logic:**
504→   504→
505→   505→```typescript
506→   506→async function checkSelfEnrichment(
507→   507→  userId: string,
508→   508→  pointId: string,
509→   509→  existingEvents: PointEvent[]
510→   510→): Promise<{ score: number; isSelfEnrich: boolean }> {
511→   511→  const pointEvents = existingEvents.filter(e => e.pointId === pointId);
512→   512→  const createEvent = pointEvents.find(e => e.eventType === 'CREATE_EVENT');
513→   513→  const userEnrichments = pointEvents.filter(
514→   514→    e => e.eventType === 'ENRICH_EVENT' && e.userId.toLowerCase() === userId.toLowerCase()
515→   515→  );
516→   516→
517→   517→  const isSelfEnrich = createEvent?.userId.toLowerCase() === userId.toLowerCase();
518→   518→  let score = 0;
519→   519→
520→   520→  if (isSelfEnrich && userEnrichments.length >= 2) score += 30;
521→   521→  if (userEnrichments.length >= 3) score += 40;
522→   522→
523→   523→  // Check temporal clustering
524→   524→  if (createEvent && userEnrichments.length > 0) {
525→   525→    const createTime = new Date(createEvent.createdAt).getTime();
526→   526→    const enrichTimes = userEnrichments.map(e => new Date(e.createdAt).getTime());
527→   527→    const minGap = Math.min(...enrichTimes.map(t => Math.abs(t - createTime)));
528→   528→
529→   529→    if (minGap < 60000) score += 20; // Enriching within 1 minute of creation
530→   530→  }
531→   531→
532→   532→  return { score, isSelfEnrich };
533→   533→}
534→   534→```
535→   535→
536→   536→**Thresholds:**
537→   537→- Self-enrichment score >= 50 -> flag, cap XP for additional enrichments
538→   538→- Self-enrichment score >= 70 -> flag + require different user to enrich
539→   539→- Single user making 3+ enrichments on same point -> block further enrichments from this user on this point
540→   540→
541→   541→**Confidence:** 80%. Self-enrichment may be legitimate (revisiting a location), but the pattern is suspicious at scale.
542→   542→
543→   543→#### Rule R-VAL-01: Field Plausibility (addresses F-POI-01, F-POI-02)
544→   544→
545→   545→**Signals:**
546→   546→- Fuel prices vs. known market range
547→   547→- Opening hours format validity
548→   548→- Provider names against known provider list
549→   549→
550→   550→**Detection Logic:**
551→   551→
552→   552→```typescript
553→   553→const CAMEROON_FUEL_PRICE_RANGE_XAF = {
554→   554→  super: { min: 500, max: 1000 },    // ~630 XAF/L in 2026
555→   555→  gasoil: { min: 450, max: 900 },
556→   556→  kerosene: { min: 400, max: 800 },
557→   557→};
558→   558→
559→   559→const KNOWN_MOBILE_MONEY_PROVIDERS = [
560→   560→  'MTN Mobile Money', 'Orange Money', 'Express Union Mobile',
561→   561→  'YUP', 'Afriland First Bank', 'UBA'
562→   562→];
563→   563→
564→   564→function validateFuelPrice(fuelType: string, priceXaf: number): 'ok' | 'flag' | 'block' {
565→   565→  const range = CAMEROON_FUEL_PRICE_RANGE_XAF[fuelType];
566→   566→  if (!range) return 'ok';
567→   567→
568→   568→  if (priceXaf <= 0 || priceXaf > 10000) return 'block';  // Impossible
569→   569→  if (priceXaf < range.min * 0.5 || priceXaf > range.max * 2) return 'flag';  // Implausible
570→   570→  return 'ok';
571→   571→}
572→   572→```
573→   573→
574→   574→**Thresholds:**
575→   575→- Price <= 0 or > 10,000 XAF -> auto-reject
576→   576→- Price outside 50%-200% of known market range -> flag
577→   577→- Unknown mobile money provider not in known list -> flag (but allow, could be new entrant)
578→   578→- Availability status changed >3 times in 24h for same POI -> flag
579→   579→
580→   580→**Confidence:** 70% for price validation. Market prices shift, so ranges must be updated periodically.
581→   581→
582→   582→#### Rule R-IP-01: IP Reputation (addresses F-LOC-02, F-ACC-02)
583→   583→
584→   584→**Signals:**
585→   585→- IP address ASN type (residential, datacenter, VPN, Tor)
586→   586→- Multiple userIds submitting from same IP within short window
587→   587→
588→   588→**Detection Logic:**
589→   589→
590→   590→```typescript
591→   591→// Enhance the existing fetchIpLocation in api/submissions/index.ts
592→   592→interface EnhancedIpInfo {
593→   593→  location: SubmissionLocation | null;
594→   594→  asn: string | null;
595→   595→  org: string | null;
596→   596→  isDatacenter: boolean;
597→   597→  isVpn: boolean;
598→   598→  isTor: boolean;
599→   599→}
600→   600→
601→   601→async function fetchEnhancedIpInfo(ip: string): Promise<EnhancedIpInfo> {
602→   602→  // Use ipapi.co (already in use) or similar service
603→   603→  const res = await fetch(`https://ipapi.co/${ip}/json/`);
604→   604→  const data = await res.json();
605→   605→
606→   606→  const org = (data.org ?? '').toLowerCase();
607→   607→  const isDatacenter = org.includes('hosting') || org.includes('cloud') ||
608→   608→    org.includes('digitalocean') || org.includes('aws') || org.includes('azure');
609→   609→  const isVpn = org.includes('vpn') || org.includes('private internet') ||
610→   610→    org.includes('nordvpn') || org.includes('express');
611→   611→
612→   612→  return {
613→   613→    location: parseLocation(data),
614→   614→    asn: data.asn ?? null,
615→   615→    org: data.org ?? null,
616→   616→    isDatacenter,
617→   617→    isVpn,
618→   618→    isTor: data.is_tor === true,
619→   619→  };
620→   620→}
621→   621→```
622→   622→
623→   623→**Thresholds:**
624→   624→- Tor exit node -> auto-block submission
625→   625→- Known VPN/datacenter ASN -> flag, increase risk score by 25
626→   626→- 3+ different userIds from same IP in 1 hour -> flag all as potential alt accounts
627→   627→
628→   628→**Confidence:** 85% for Tor/datacenter. 60% for VPN (many legitimate users in Africa use VPNs for connectivity reasons).
629→   629→
630→   630→#### Rule R-GRA-01: Collusion Graph Analysis (addresses F-XP-03)
631→   631→
632→   632→**Signals:**
633→   633→- User-to-point bipartite graph: which users interact with which points
634→   634→- Reciprocal enrichment patterns: A enriches B's points AND B enriches A's points
635→   635→- Temporal coordination: submissions from different users on same points within narrow windows
636→   636→
637→   637→**Detection Logic:**
638→   638→
639→   639→```sql
640→   640→-- Find reciprocal enrichment pairs
641→   641→WITH enrichments AS (
642→   642→  SELECT
643→   643→    e.user_id AS enricher,
644→   644→    c.user_id AS creator,
645→   645→    e.point_id
646→   646→  FROM point_events e
647→   647→  JOIN point_events c ON e.point_id = c.point_id
648→   648→    AND c.event_type = 'CREATE_EVENT'
649→   649→  WHERE e.event_type = 'ENRICH_EVENT'
650→   650→    AND e.user_id != c.user_id
651→   651→),
652→   652→pairs AS (
653→   653→  SELECT
654→   654→    enricher AS user_a,
655→   655→    creator AS user_b,
656→   656→    COUNT(*) AS a_enriches_b
657→   657→  FROM enrichments
658→   658→  GROUP BY enricher, creator
659→   659→)
660→   660→SELECT
661→   661→  p1.user_a,
662→   662→  p1.user_b,
663→   663→  p1.a_enriches_b,
664→   664→  COALESCE(p2.a_enriches_b, 0) AS b_enriches_a
665→   665→FROM pairs p1
666→   666→LEFT JOIN pairs p2
667→   667→  ON p1.user_a = p2.user_b AND p1.user_b = p2.user_a
668→   668→WHERE p1.a_enriches_b >= 3
669→   669→  AND COALESCE(p2.a_enriches_b, 0) >= 3
670→   670→ORDER BY (p1.a_enriches_b + COALESCE(p2.a_enriches_b, 0)) DESC;
671→   671→```
672→   672→
673→   673→**Thresholds:**
674→   674→- Reciprocal enrichment between two users >= 3 times each -> flag both accounts
675→   675→- 3+ users all enriching each other's points >= 2 times -> escalate as collusion ring
676→   676→- Cluster of users with >80% of their enrichments going to other cluster members -> auto-flag all
677→   677→
678→   678→**Confidence:** 75%. Legitimate community behavior (neighbors validating each other's submissions) can look like collusion. Requires manual review.
679→   679→
680→   680→---
681→   681→
682→   682→## 3. Risk Scoring Model
683→   683→
684→   684→### 3.1 Submission Risk Score (0-100)
685→   685→
686→   686→Every submission receives a composite risk score computed from five trust dimensions. Higher score = higher risk = more likely fraudulent.
687→   687→
688→   688→```
689→   689→SubmissionRiskScore = w_loc * LocationRisk
690→   690→                    + w_pho * PhotoRisk
691→   691→                    + w_tmp * TemporalRisk
692→   692→                    + w_usr * UserRisk
693→   693→                    + w_bhv * BehavioralRisk
694→   694→```
695→   695→
696→   696→#### Component Weights (Initial Calibration)
697→   697→
698→   698→| Component | Weight | Rationale |
699→   699→|---|---|---|
700→   700→| Location Trust (LocationRisk) | 0.25 | GPS/IP/EXIF triangulation is the strongest objective signal |
701→   701→| Photo Trust (PhotoRisk) | 0.25 | Photo evidence is the primary proof of physical presence |
702→   702→| Temporal Trust (TemporalRisk) | 0.15 | Velocity and timing patterns |
703→   703→| User Trust (UserRisk) | 0.20 | Account age, history, prior fraud flags |
704→   704→| Behavioral Trust (BehavioralRisk) | 0.15 | Submission patterns, enrichment behavior |
705→   705→
706→   706→#### 3.1.1 Location Risk (0-100)
707→   707→
708→   708→```typescript
709→   709→function computeLocationRisk(params: {
710→   710→  submissionLocation: SubmissionLocation | null;
711→   711→  photoExifGps: SubmissionLocation | null;
712→   712→  ipLocation: SubmissionLocation | null;
713→   713→  effectiveLocation: SubmissionLocation;
714→   714→}): number {
715→   715→  let risk = 0;
716→   716→
717→   717→  // No submission GPS provided (using fallback)
718→   718→  if (!params.submissionLocation) risk += 15;
719→   719→
720→   720→  // No EXIF GPS in photo
721→   721→  if (!params.photoExifGps) risk += 20;
722→   722→
723→   723→  // No IP location resolved
724→   724→  if (!params.ipLocation) risk += 10;
725→   725→
726→   726→  // Submission-to-photo GPS mismatch (if both present)
727→   727→  if (params.submissionLocation && params.photoExifGps) {
728→   728→    const dist = haversineKm(params.submissionLocation, params.photoExifGps);
729→   729→    if (dist > 1) risk += 40;       // Beyond 1km threshold
730→   730→    else if (dist > 0.5) risk += 15; // Marginal
731→   731→  }
732→   732→
733→   733→  // IP-to-effective location mismatch
734→   734→  if (params.ipLocation) {
735→   735→    const dist = haversineKm(params.ipLocation, params.effectiveLocation);
736→   736→    if (dist > 50) risk += 30;
737→   737→    else if (dist > 20) risk += 10;
738→   738→  }
739→   739→
740→   740→  return Math.min(100, risk);
741→   741→}
742→   742→```
743→   743→
744→   744→#### 3.1.2 Photo Risk (0-100)
745→   745→
746→   746→```typescript
747→   747→function computePhotoRisk(params: {
748→   748→  hasExifGps: boolean;
749→   749→  hasExifTimestamp: boolean;
750→   750→  hasDeviceInfo: boolean;
751→   751→  imageHash: string;
752→   752→  existingHashes: Set<string>;
753→   753→  imageDimensions: { width: number; height: number };
754→   754→  isLowEndDevice: boolean;
755→   755→}): number {
756→   756→  let risk = 0;
757→   757→
758→   758→  // Photo hash already exists for different point
759→   759→  if (params.existingHashes.has(params.imageHash)) risk += 80;
760→   760→
761→   761→  // Missing EXIF metadata
762→   762→  if (!params.hasExifGps) risk += 15;
763→   763→  if (!params.hasExifTimestamp) risk += 10;
764→   764→  if (!params.hasDeviceInfo) risk += 10;
765→   765→
766→   766→  // Screenshot dimensions (common phone screen resolutions)
767→   767→  const { width, height } = params.imageDimensions;
768→   768→  const isScreenshotRatio = (
769→   769→    (width === 1080 && height === 2400) || // Common Android screenshot
770→   770→    (width === 1170 && height === 2532) || // iPhone 12/13 screenshot
771→   771→    (width === 1284 && height === 2778)    // iPhone 12/13 Pro Max screenshot
772→   772→  );
773→   773→  if (isScreenshotRatio) risk += 15;
774→   774→
775→   775→  // Mitigate for low-end devices
776→   776→  if (params.isLowEndDevice && risk > 0 && risk <= 35) {
777→   777→    risk = Math.max(0, risk - 10);
778→   778→  }
779→   779→
780→   780→  return Math.min(100, risk);
781→   781→}
782→   782→```
783→   783→
784→   784→#### 3.1.3 Temporal Risk (0-100)
785→   785→
786→   786→```typescript
787→   787→function computeTemporalRisk(params: {
788→   788→  recentSubmissionCount15min: number;
789→   789→  recentSubmissionCount1hr: number;
790→   790→  lastSubmissionLocation: SubmissionLocation | null;
791→   791→  lastSubmissionTime: Date | null;
792→   792→  currentLocation: SubmissionLocation;
793→   793→  currentTime: Date;
794→   794→}): number {
795→   795→  let risk = 0;
796→   796→
797→   797→  // Velocity
798→   798→  if (params.recentSubmissionCount15min > 10) risk += 50;
799→   799→  else if (params.recentSubmissionCount15min > 5) risk += 25;
800→   800→  else if (params.recentSubmissionCount15min > 3) risk += 10;
801→   801→
802→   802→  // Impossible travel
803→   803→  if (params.lastSubmissionLocation && params.lastSubmissionTime) {
804→   804→    const distKm = haversineKm(params.lastSubmissionLocation, params.currentLocation);
805→   805→    const hoursElapsed = (params.currentTime.getTime() - params.lastSubmissionTime.getTime()) / 3600000;
806→   806→    if (hoursElapsed > 0) {
807→   807→      const speedKmh = distKm / hoursElapsed;
808→   808→      if (speedKmh > 200) risk += 50;
809→   809→      else if (speedKmh > 80) risk += 25;
810→   810→    }
811→   811→  }
812→   812→
813→   813→  // Late-night submissions (less likely to be legitimate fieldwork)
814→   814→  const hour = params.currentTime.getUTCHours() + 1; // UTC+1 for Cameroon
815→   815→  if (hour >= 23 || hour < 5) risk += 10;
816→   816→
817→   817→  return Math.min(100, risk);
818→   818→}
819→   819→```
820→   820→
821→   821→#### 3.1.4 User Risk (0-100)
822→   822→
823→   823→```typescript
824→   824→function computeUserRisk(params: {
825→   825→  accountAgeDays: number;
826→   826→  totalSubmissions: number;
827→   827→  priorFraudFlags: number;
828→   828→  priorRejections: number;
829→   829→  userTrustScore: number; // 0-100, see section 3.2
830→   830→}): number {
831→   831→  let risk = 0;
832→   832→
833→   833→  // New account penalty
834→   834→  if (params.accountAgeDays < 1) risk += 25;
835→   835→  else if (params.accountAgeDays < 7) risk += 15;
836→   836→  else if (params.accountAgeDays < 30) risk += 5;
837→   837→
838→   838→  // No submission history
839→   839→  if (params.totalSubmissions === 0) risk += 15;
840→   840→
841→   841→  // Prior fraud history
842→   842→  risk += Math.min(40, params.priorFraudFlags * 10);
843→   843→  risk += Math.min(20, params.priorRejections * 5);
844→   844→
845→   845→  // Inverse of user trust score
846→   846→  risk += Math.round((100 - params.userTrustScore) * 0.2);
847→   847→
848→   848→  return Math.min(100, risk);
849→   849→}
850→   850→```
851→   851→
852→   852→#### 3.1.5 Behavioral Risk (0-100)
853→   853→
854→   854→```typescript
855→   855→function computeBehavioralRisk(params: {
856→   856→  selfEnrichmentCount: number;
857→   857→  samePointEnrichments: number;
858→   858→  categoryDistribution: Map<string, number>; // how many of each category
859→   859→  totalSubmissions: number;
860→   860→  deviceIdSharedWithOtherUsers: boolean;
861→   861→  ipSharedWithOtherUsers: boolean;
862→   862→}): number {
863→   863→  let risk = 0;
864→   864→
865→   865→  // Self-enrichment pattern
866→   866→  if (params.selfEnrichmentCount > 5) risk += 30;
867→   867→  else if (params.selfEnrichmentCount > 2) risk += 15;
868→   868→
869→   869→  // Excessive enrichments on single point
870→   870→  if (params.samePointEnrichments > 3) risk += 25;
871→   871→
872→   872→  // Monoculture (only submitting one category could indicate targeted farming)
873→   873→  if (params.totalSubmissions > 10) {
874→   874→    const maxCategoryPct = Math.max(...params.categoryDistribution.values()) / params.totalSubmissions;
875→   875→    if (maxCategoryPct > 0.95) risk += 10;
876→   876→  }
877→   877→
878→   878→  // Device/IP sharing signals
879→   879→  if (params.deviceIdSharedWithOtherUsers) risk += 15;
880→   880→  if (params.ipSharedWithOtherUsers) risk += 10;
881→   881→
882→   882→  return Math.min(100, risk);
883→   883→}
884→   884→```
885→   885→
886→   886→### 3.2 User Trust Score (0-100)
887→   887→
888→   888→A long-term reputation score that builds with legitimate contributions and decays with fraud signals.
889→   889→
890→   890→```typescript
891→   891→interface UserTrustProfile {
892→   892→  userId: string;
893→   893→  trustScore: number;           // 0-100, starts at 50
894→   894→  totalApproved: number;        // Submissions that passed review
